# [#25] Security Audit for Payment and Payout Systems

> **GitHub**: https://github.com/kanya01/COLABS/issues/25
> **Opened**: 2026-01-14
> **Labels**: `epic:services-workflow` `priority:critical` `security` `critical`
> **Assignee**: —
> **Ref**: Services Workflow Implementation Issues #19

## Description

Conduct security review and implement security best practices for payment handling across the platform.

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Verify webhook signature validation
- [ ] Implement idempotency keys for payments
- [ ] Add rate limiting on payment endpoints
- [ ] Verify authorization checks on all endpoints
- [ ] Audit server-side validation for all inputs
- [ ] Check amount limits and reasonability
- [ ] Verify no sensitive data in logs
- [ ] Ensure HTTPS enforcement
- [ ] Review CSRF protection
- [ ] Audit database query security (SQL injection)
- [ ] Review file upload security
- [ ] Implement Content Security Policy headers
- [ ] Add monitoring for suspicious activities
- [ ] Document security considerations
- [ ] Create security testing checklist

## Related Notes

- [[Docs/services/STRIPE_INTEGRATION]] — Stripe webhook and payment setup
- [[Docs/services/SERVICES_WORKFLOW_ENABLEMENT_PLAN]] — Phase 7
- [[Docs/services/FILE_UPLOAD_GUIDE]] — File upload security context
