# [#21] Comprehensive Backend Testing for Services Workflow

> **GitHub**: https://github.com/kanya01/COLABS/issues/21
> **Opened**: 2026-01-14
> **Labels**: `backend` `epic:services-workflow` `testing` `quality`
> **Assignee**: —
> **Ref**: Services Workflow Implementation Issues #15

## Description

Create a comprehensive Rails test suite for all models and controllers related to the services workflow.

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] `ServiceTier` model tests — validations, associations, enums
- [ ] `Order` model tests — status transitions, calculations, validations
- [ ] `OrderRevision` model tests — limit enforcement, numbering
- [ ] `OrderDeliverable` model tests — file attachments
- [ ] `SellerProfile` model tests — earnings calculations, account status
- [ ] `Earning` model tests — platform fee calculations, status
- [ ] `Payout` model tests — validations, status
- [ ] `PaymentsController` tests — intent creation, webhooks
- [ ] `StripeConnectController` tests — account creation, onboarding
- [ ] `PayoutsController` tests — balance checks, payout creation
- [ ] `OrdersController` tests — CRUD, authorization
- [ ] `OrderRevisionsController` tests — limit enforcement
- [ ] `OrderDeliverablesController` tests — upload, download
- [ ] Achieve >90% code coverage on new code
- [ ] Add fixtures for all new models
- [ ] Mock Stripe API calls appropriately

## Related Notes

- [[Docs/testing/TESTING_STRATEGY]] — Coverage target (>90%)
- [[Docs/testing/TESTING_GUIDE]] — How to run RSpec tests
- [[Docs/services/SERVICES_WORKFLOW_ENABLEMENT_PLAN]] — Phase 6.1 and 6.2
- [[Docs/design/SYSTEM_ONTOLOGY]] — Full model reference
